The &lt;junit&gt; and &lt;batchtest&gt; tasks can do what you want. Is there a 
reason you don&#39;t want to use &lt;junit&gt;? Presumably in the future, it could 
have more and better features. Not only that, why not reuse someone 
else&#39;s good work?

I would use &lt;junit&gt; until I needed it to do something it didn&#39;t do.
